<ns2731:section xmlns:ns2731="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.networkServices.dhcp.client">

	<ns2732:title xmlns:ns2732="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Dynamic network configuration using dhcp</ns2732:title>
	<ns2733:para xmlns:ns2733="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	The clients are typically configured via the network configuration. Alternatively, the <ns2734:emphasis xmlns:ns2734="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="strong">dhcpcd [network interface]</ns2734:emphasis> tool can be used to configure the specified network interface via DHCP.
	</ns2733:para>
